# 030 — graph-core

## Purpose

`graph-core` defines the data model of a graph. It is pure TypeScript with zero side effects.

## Allowed

- Type definitions: `GraphDefinition`, `NodeDefinition`, `EdgeDefinition`, `GraphState`, `GraphValidationError`
- Zod schemas for all definitions
- A `GraphValidator` that validates a `GraphDefinition` and returns typed errors
- Pure utility functions (no I/O)

## Forbidden

- No database access, no HTTP calls, no file system access
- No NestJS, no Next.js, no React
- No LLM calls
- No imports from `graph-runtime` or any app
- No runtime execution logic

## Conditions

- Conditions in edges must be named strings, e.g. `"hasCriticalRisk"`.
- No inline JavaScript functions or expressions in graph definitions.
- Condition resolution is the responsibility of `graph-runtime`'s `ConditionRegistry`.

## Versioning

- `GraphDefinition` must carry a `version` field (semver string).
- Schema changes must be backward-compatible or introduce a new version.